title: Bias, garbage, and CP
text: YouTube was the pinnacle of creativity about a decade ago. Now, they are actively manipulating what can and cannot be posted based on whether they agree with messages told. They bolster fake and manipulated articles while also allowing straight up porn on their platform. A straight up nude b-hole was shown without age restriction, but opinions in politics are canned? YouTube also allows doxing if you are famous, while hammering the lesser known channels. They also pump ads full of sexist messaging against men (and sometimes women) which is a violation of the rules of YouTube. Overall, YouTube changed from a free speech platform, to one that has porn, manipulated media, and promotes depression in young adults.
